An aspirant of the Peoples Redemption Party (PRP) Abubakar Abdullahi Shamaki for Birnin Kebbi, Kalgo and Bunza federal constituency has said that as a new breed politician he joined full-time politics because he noticed a gap between the government and poor masses.Speaking at his residence in Birnin Kebbi said poor representation is responsible for the lack of welfare and infrastructure as evidence of quality representations. He noted that youth must be meaningfully engaged to put paid to restiveness “we have been able to while in active service secured employments to at 50 graduates from Kebbi state, this we intend to continue when we win elections”. Shamaki added that the none literate class will be engaged through skills acquisition and microfinancing outlets will be established in the three local governments that made up his constituency as a job and wealth creation strategy. -Advertisement- He stated that his constituency projects will be based on the needs assessment of the people because each community has its own peculiar demands. On the Chances of PRP winning elections in 2023 he said the party is famous and one of the oldest political parties is now coming as a third force to wrestle power from both the ruling All progressives Congress APC and the opposition peoples democratic party PDP who have woefully failed Nigerians in all sectors. He pointed out that winning the primaries encouraged him to sit up and not to give up in order to rescue Kebbi.